snippet: Catherine Ashton, the lead negotiator for the six-nation group bargaining with Iran over its contentious uranium enrichment program, did not offer specifics about talks on May 23 in Baghdad.
abstract: Catherine Ashton, lead negotiator for the six-nation group bargaining with Iran over its contentious uranium enrichment program, says she aspires to achieve 'the beginnings of the end' of the dispute at the next meeting held in Baghdad.
lead_paragraph: Catherine Ashton, the lead negotiator for the six-nation group bargaining with Iran over its contentious uranium enrichment program, did not offer specifics about talks on May 23 in Baghdad.

headline.seo: Nuclear Negotiator Seeks ‘Beginnings of the End’ of Iran Dispute
headline.main: Nuclear Negotiator Seeks ‘Beginnings of the End’ of Iran Dispute
